<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
I had a princess quest for 6 druj (the prison with three in a corridor on each side) in Mdr 55. I used shake to give myself a clear shot at the druj. The princess square was hit by rubble and the princess disappeared (I had telepathy). After I killed all six druj with fireflash the princess thanked me and said "take this". No choice, no reward, no stairs, and the glass walls of the prison are all intact. The princess square is now lava. ^q says that the druj are all dead, but the quest is still listed there. <p>
Anonymous- This happens to me all the time.  You generally need to leave the level, then quit out of the game and reload your save file, and go back down to bring her back to life.  You can leave the level and come back in the same game without reloading, but while the 6 druj will reappear (and you'll hear the princess screaming away) she will still be dead when you get there (and will still offer you a reward but drop nothing).  This is particularly annoying on those occasions where finishing the quest gives you the only stairway down, as that also won't appear until you save a 'living' princess. 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


